{
  "stem": "14168.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had their passports shipped to Peru-- but it didn't-- in order to get visas, it was impossible.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In-- meanwhile, a friend of mine had, like quite a few other refugees, had- had landed in Bolivia, which was adjacent to Peru, just across Lake Tititcaca.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he said, well, if you're lucky you might be able to help your folks from here.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I pulled up stakes in Peru, crossed Lake Titicaca, and settled down in La Paz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "After a few hours-- a few-- few weeks, I was able to get a-- an audience with the president of Bolivia, Quintanilla, through the recommendations of my landlady's son, who had gone to school with him.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Bolivia.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said he was-- must have been impressed by my Spanish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said, OK, remarkable you are one of the few who speak Spanish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I told him that I like the language of Cervantes, and I enjoyed very much being in Bolivia and finding a new homeland there, and that I wished for my folks to join me.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he looked at me, and then he called-- he pressed a button.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He said, take this gentleman to my secretary.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I want him to give me-- I want him to give you the names of his people, and the visa is granted.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I was able to get that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then-- Were you only able to give the names of people for whom you already had the passports, because they had shipped them to you?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, the passports had to be shipped back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because, in the meanwhile, the steamship companies had all been warned against getting-- taking passengers on board whose visas had not been issued in Germany.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And these visas would not have been issued in Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
